  "text": "The strategies suggested for addressing silent refusals differed between men and women participants, related to the gendered nature of household decision-making in this community [CITATION_1] . Many women felt that community leaders such as village elders and chiefs should arbitrate between FWs and silent refusals, men saw such arbitration as challenging their decisionmaking authority:",
